Kenyan Drought Area Hit by Flooding; Nine People Killed, Daily Nation Says

-- B y   P a u l   R i c h a r d s o n
-- 
2011-08-16T04:24:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-16/kenyan-drought-area-hit-by-flooding-nine-people-killed-daily-nation-says.html
At least nine people died in
northwestern  Kenya  when a minibus they were traveling in was
swept away by a flash flood, the  Daily Nation  reported, citing
Turkana West District Commissioner Patrick Muriira.  The Nawatom River burst its banks after rain fell on Aug.
14 in an area that has experienced a drought and faced the
threat of famine, the Nairobi-based newspaper said.  In the southwestern city of Kisumu, on the banks of Lake
Victoria, at least 100 families were forced to flee their homes
that were damaged by floods, the newspaper said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  